If you create a Webhooks using the below API (with history logging being "true") from team account level, the hook is being created, however, the history logging is not showing due to some browser console logs error.

!3545609826-read_only_hook.png|thumbnail!

*API CURL Command*:

{code}
#!curl
curl -v -H "Authorization: Bearer ACCESS_TOKEN" -X POST -H "Content-Type: application/json" https://api.bitbucket.org/2.0/teams/team_username/hooks/ -d &#x27;{"read_only":true,"description":"some_desc","url":"https://webhooks-testing.com/hooks","skip_cert_verification":false,"history_enabled":true,"active":true,"type":"webhook_subscription","events":["repo:push"]}&#x27;
{code}

*API Doc*: https://developer.atlassian.com/bitbucket/api/2/reference/resource/teams/%7Busername%7D/hooks

h3. Expected Result
The created hook should show history logging.

h3. Actual Result
The created hook is not showing history logging.

The contents of a README.md file in the root of a project can be viewed from 3 different pages.

# Overview
# Source
# File viewer

I&#x27;d expect the generated Markdown to be identical for all 3 pages. But the contents of the &#x27;File viewer&#x27; differ from the two others.

In my repo I have a numeric list defined as:

{code}
#!markdown

The filename is based on:
1. The prefix you specify as the second argument of the command. In this case that is `demo`.
2. The name of the sheet you are downloading. in this case that is `sheet1`.
3. The &#x27;last modified date&#x27; of the downloaded document in the format `YmdHis`.  

{code}

On the &#x27;Overview&#x27; and &#x27;Source&#x27; page this is rendered as:

{code}
#!text
The filename is based on: 1. The prefix you specify as the second argument of the command. In this case that is demo. 2. The name of the sheet you are downloading. in this case that is sheet1. 3. The &#x27;last modified date&#x27; of the downloaded document in the format YmdHis.
{code}

Only in the File Viewer it&#x27;s correctly displayed as:

{code}
#!text
The filename is based on:
1. The prefix you specify as the second argument of the command. In this case that is `demo`.
2. The name of the sheet you are downloading. in this case that is `sheet1`.
3. The &#x27;last modified date&#x27; of the downloaded document in the format `YmdHis`.  
{code}

